	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Sik</b> [ Fri Oct 17, 2014 2:27 am ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: Genesis region hacking?</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Go to address $0001F0 in the ROM, then change the three bytes there to the ASCII string &quot;JUE&quot;. Yeah, that's pretty much all there's to it, most games with region lockout look at the ROM header instead of being hardcoded (that's what you get when everybody uses the off-the-shelf routine).<br /><br />A few games are hardcoded and that method won't work on those, in that case your only option is to hack the game itself =/ (and this procedure will be unique to each game).

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


